.TH CLIP_CLIENT 1 "February 2026" "ws-camerad 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
clip_client \- extract video clips from ws-camerad
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B clip_client
[\fIstart_offset\fR] [\fIend_offset\fR] [\fIsocket_path\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B clip_client
connects to the ws-camerad daemon and requests extraction of a video clip
from the ring buffer.
.PP
Time offsets are specified in seconds relative to the current time.
Negative values refer to the past (already recorded), positive values
request continued recording into the future.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I start_offset
Seconds before current time to start clip (default: -5)
.TP
.I end_offset
Seconds after current time to end clip (default: 5)
.TP
.I socket_path
Path to daemon control socket (default: /run/ws-camerad/control.sock)
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Extract 10 seconds of video (5 seconds before and after now):
.B clip_client -5 5
.TP
Extract last 30 seconds:
.B clip_client -30 0
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ws-camerad (8),
.BR still_client (1),
.BR frame_consumer (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Camera Daemon Contributors
